 *
 * Thingy:91 X adaptation layer for att_flash_partitions.dtsi.
 *
 * The Thingy:91 X base board DTS (thingy91x_nrf9151_partition.dtsi)
 * defines an `external_flash_partition` node in the external SPI-NOR
 * flash, occupying the address range we need for our own settings /
 * littlefs / external-flash layout. Remove it here so the shared file
 * can place its own partitions without label or address collisions.
 *
 * Everything else the shared file needs (the `flash_ext` label, the
 * b0/s0/s1 partitions and `fmfu_storage_partition`) already exists in
 * the base DTS, so nothing more needs to be added.
 *
 * Must be included BEFORE att_flash_partitions.dtsi.
 */

/delete-node/ &external_flash_partition;
